The weird two-pronged concept album thing of In League honestly didn't work out that well, but of the songs that tie directly into it, this is probably my favorite. I also grew up pretty near the Sac and Fox rez, where the Meskwaki casino is, so it has a bit of personal clout there.

Title: Laura
Comment:
30 monthly listeners.

In 2020 Mega Emotion recorded personal tracks for the first 50 people to buy a copy of their EP on cassette, in a project called #fromMEtoyou. They invited the recipients (in this case someone called Laura) to give them details of their life, and then wrote the song around that. This one is about "growing up gay in a small northern village. It‚Äôs about the girl at school who never really knew how you felt, about unrequited love, and still burning inside."
